records.addlTxt: Transcript PLEA AND SENTENCING HEARING  commencing MAY 8, 2014 received and filed.  Original transcript in case file 14CF1017  (28 Pages).

Defendant Kendrae D Buie in court with attorney Nathan Opland-Dobs.  Defendant Kendrae D Buie in custody.  Thomas L. Potter appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  

AS TO COUNT 1 AND COUNT 2:  DISMISSED.

AS TO COUNT 3 AND 4
Defendant changes plea to GUILTY. Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty. Court found that defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights. Plea questionnaire received and filed. Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea. Court found defendant guilty as charged in the information and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record. Defendant is advised he is a convicted felon and may not possess any firearms. Defendant is advised he is unable to vote in any election until civil rights are restored. Defendant further advised that if he is not a US citizen deportation is possible.  

Sentencing proceeds. Statements made by the State, defense and defendant. 
.
AS TO COUNT 3
The Court sentenced defendant to serve a term of IMPRISONMENT in the Wisconsin State Prisons for 6 YEARS and 6 MONTHS, CONCURRENT TO ANY OTHER SENTENCE.  INITIAL CONFINEMENT of 2 YEARS and 6 MONTHS and EXTENDED SUPERVISION of 4 YEARS with the following conditions:

AS TO COUNT 4
The Court sentenced defendant to serve a term of IMPRISONMENT in the Wisconsin State Prisons for 6 YEARS and 6 MONTHS, CONCURRENT to #3 and ANY OTHER SENTENCE.  INITIAL CONFINEMENT of 2 YEARS and 6 MONTHS and EXTENDED SUPERVISION of 4 YEARS with the following conditions:

-no contact with victims, Brandon W (COUNT 1), Ladanna B (COUNT 2), AMY B (COUNT 3), PAULINE G (COUNT 4);
-provide DNA sample;
-pay MANDATORY DNA surcharge, (COUNTS 3 and 4), failure to pay shall result in a civil judgment being entered;
-pay all court costs, fees, and surcharges (COUNTS 3 and 4), failure to pay shall result in a civil judgment being entered;
-pay restitution in the amount of $100.00 to Amy B (COUNT 3),and  $1000.00to Pauline G (COUNT 4); failure to pay shall result in a civil judgment being entered;
-25% of prison funds to go toward restitution and all other monetary obligation thereafter;
-obtain/maintain fulltime employment/education/vocation;
-pay all applicable fees of supervision (COUNTS 3 and 4); failure to pay shall result in a civil judgment being entered.
-
-  A payment plan for all monetary obligations is to be established by Department of Corrections, Probation and Parole.  All unpaid monetary obligation balances will convert to a civil judgment.
-  Cash Bail in the amount of $3000.00, posted on 02-16-2014 in case 14CF404 is to be applied to restitution/all monetary obligations in both 14CF404 and 14CF1017.  Any amounts remaining after application to restitution/all monetary obligations in both cases is to be returned to person posting bail.
-  Firearm/Voting Rights/Civil Judgment Warnings given.
-
Credit given for 88 days (COUNTS 3 and 4) time served.
Court advised defendant on Extended Confinement or "bad time".
Defendant IS eligible for Challenge Incarceration Program.
Defendant is NOT eligible for the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program.
